			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Swipely, recently named by Providence Business News as one of the &quot;Best Places to Work in Rhode Island&quot; and by Forbes as &quot;One of America&#39;s Most Promising Companies&quot;,&nbsp; is looking for an experienced Director of Design and UX to join our rapidly growing Providence, RI based team.</strong></p>
<p>
<strong>About Swipely</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
An award-winning place to work, named by Providence Business Newsas one of the &quot;Best Places to Work in Rhode Island&quot; and by Forbes as&quot;One of America&#39;s Most Promising Companies&quot;</li>
<li>
The fastest-growing Silicon Valley-funded technology company in Rhode Island</li>
<li>
Founded, managed and backed by successful veterans of Microsoft, Google, eBay, LinkedIn, Facebook, Living Social and Seamless.com</li>
<li>
Disrupting a massive, growing $70 billion market for payments with innovation</li>
<li>
Helping hundreds of renowned local businesses better understand customers and grow sales while transforming the expense of accepting payments into a valuable marketing investment</li>
<li>
A fun and exciting start-up that empowers its people and offers growth potential</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Your Mission</strong></p>
<p>
Our success depends upon two key product goals with which you will deeply engage.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>First,</strong> we very recently launched new products that few of our merchants have experienced yet, including our campaign insights and reputation monitoring systems.&nbsp; Over the summer, you will engage with merchants, unveiling our are latest product features and forming an understanding of how we can best evolve them to meet merchants&#39; needs.&nbsp; Through your efforts and our collective response, our merchants will be so excited and thrilled by Swipely that they will sing high praise of our products and services to all of their friends.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Second</strong>, by the end of the year we will be embarking upon a new product direction that further distinguishes us from our current competition.&nbsp; Just as Swipely has revolutionized the payment processing space, you will be deeply involved in identifying and designing a solution to local merchants&#39; next biggest pain point, empowering Swipely to disrupt another industry ripe for new ideas.&nbsp; You will be instrumental in realizing our vision of launching the world&rsquo;s first Business Operating System.</p>
<p>
<strong>An ideal candidate:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Has an exceptional portfolio of shipped software products, containing examples of data visualization, visual creativity and the ability to make complicated functionality easy to use</li>
<li>
Experience building teams and developing careers of creative professionals</li>
<li>
A passion for making users&#39; lives easier, and leveraging user research and usability studies to do so</li>
<li>
Drives the transition from whiteboard sessions and high-level requirements to specific designs, with flow diagrams, wireframes and interaction prototypes</li>
<li>
The ability to deliver detailed pixel-level comps, redlines, and static assets optimized for web delivery</li>
<li>
A strong understanding of both the potential and limitation of web technologies (HTML/CSS/JavaScript) (although coding is not required)</li>
<li>
Experience designing native mobile and responsive web applications a plus</li>
<li>
Excitement around Swipely&rsquo;s mission to help local merchants leverage big data to grow their businesses</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>The Director of Design and UX will:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Work with the senior Management Team to define strategic product direction</li>
<li>
Collaborate with the Product team to define feature concepts, hypotheses and success criteria ; iterate on wireframes, flow diagrams, and specifications</li>
<li>
Engage with existing customers, performing usability studies with to gather feedback on current and conceptual product features ; take pragmatic action based on the results</li>
<li>
Execute with the Engineering team, delivering&nbsp; and iterating on detailed visual/interaction specifications, and ensure fit and finish of the shipping product</li>
<li>
Support the Sales and Marketing team looking to build collateral that convey the value props of the product</li>
<li>
Define and manage brand identity across all products and publications</li>
<li>
This position will report to the Vice President of Product</li>
</ul>
